Goal is to provide the process as part of the truth info so we can compare distributions / make sensitivity studies in terms of the different types of Geant processes.

Working with files in /pnfs/dune/persistent/physicsgroups/dunendsim/abooth/nd-production/MicroProdN4p1/

The Process for a particle describes the process that created it. 
  * https://github.com/NuSoftHEP/nusimdata/blob/main/nusimdata/SimulationBase/MCParticle.h
  * So, we ask the daughters of the Primary what their process is. If we ask a Primary for its process, it will be "Primary".
  * As I understand it, the Process comes directly from Geant rather than from some enums provided by us in novasoft. For example "hFritiofCaptureAtRest" 
  * https://github.com/Geant4/geant4/blob/master/source/global/management/src/G4PhysicsModelCatalog.cc

In NOvA I do this like so:
  art::Ptr<sim::Particle> hitParticle;
  int numdaughters = hitParticle->NumberDaughters();
  # use backtracker to get the daughter
  for (int nd=0; nd<numdaughters; ++nd){
    const sim::Particle* daughter = bt->TrackIDToParticle( hitParticle->Daughter(nd) );
    std::cout<< " Daughter "<<nd<< " process: " << daughter->Process() <<std::endl;
  }

